html
    head
        title Import a Tilt Datasheet
        link(rel='stylesheet' href='/styles.css')
    body
        h1 Import Tilt Datasheet
        p You can download/export the Google Sheets data from a previous Tilt run as a CSV, and upload it here. The data will be saved into the database and you can view the graphed data as normal.
        
        form(action='/upload' enctype='multipart/form-data' method='POST')
            div
                label(for='beer-name') Beer Name
                input(id='beer-name' name='beer-name')
            div
                label(for='tilt-data-csv') Upload one or more CSV files
                input(id='tilt-data-csv' name='tilt-data-csv' type='file' accept='text/csv')
                span.help-text Make sure that you are importing only the 'Data' sheet from your Google Sheet.
            input(type='submit' value='Upload CSV(s)')
